01:04.730 --> 01:07.199
<i>Deborah?</i>

01:07.300 --> 01:09.325
- Where you been?
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry, T.

01:09.435 --> 01:11.335
- Are you cheating on me?
- No, no! I'm not cheating on you.

01:11.437 --> 01:13.928
- What...
- Stop it! What are you doing?

01:14.040 --> 01:16.031
- T! Stop it!
- You ain't leaving me!

01:16.142 --> 01:19.077
- Who is it?
- Nobody! It's you! I hate you!

01:19.178 --> 01:22.204
T. Ray, just let me go!

01:22.315 --> 01:25.341
No!

01:25.451 --> 01:28.007
<i>T. Ray, damn it!
Get off me!</i>

01:28.187 --> 01:29.714
Lily!

01:37.697 --> 01:41.064
<i>I killed my mother when I was four years old.</i>

01:41.167 --> 01:43.863
<i>That's what I knew about myself.</i>

01:43.970 --> 01:46.837
<i>She was all I wanted,</i>
<i>and I took her away.</i>

01:48.141 --> 01:50.041
<i>Nothin' else much mattered.</i>

02:38.457 --> 02:39.924
- T. Ray!
- What?

02:40.026 --> 02:42.187
There's bees in my room!
Hundreds of' em! You've gotta see!

02:42.295 --> 02:44.786
- What is it? Jesus Christ, Lily.
- They're in my room! Come see.

02:44.897 --> 02:46.865
What?

02:57.944 --> 02:59.844
Goddamn it, Lily.
This ain't funny.

02:59.946 --> 03:02.346
But they were here.
They were flyin' everywhere.

03:02.448 --> 03:04.814
You wake me again,
I'm gonna get out the grits.

03:04.917 --> 03:06.885
You hear me?

03:09.755 --> 03:11.723
<i>Goddamn it.</i>

03:24.203 --> 03:26.763
<i>The bees came the summer of'64...</i>

03:26.873 --> 03:31.742
<i>The summer I turned 14 and my whole life</i>
<i>went spinnin' off into a whole new orbit.</i>

03:31.844 --> 03:35.644
<i>Lookin' back on it,</i>
<i>I wanna say they were sent to me.</i>

03:35.748 --> 03:40.208
<i>I wanna say they showed up like</i>
<i>the Angel Gabriel appearing to the Virgin Mary.</i>

03:40.319 --> 03:42.583
<i>I know it's forward to compare</i>
<i>my small life to hers...</i>

03:44.024 --> 03:47.983
<i>but I have good reason</i>
<i>to believe she wouldn't mind.</i>

04:16.089 --> 04:19.582
So, um, my birthday is tomorrow.

04:21.995 --> 04:24.590
Most girls want...

04:24.698 --> 04:29.726
one of them little silver charm bracelets
they have down at the mercantile.

04:29.837 --> 04:33.432
Think I'm the only girl in junior high
doesn't have one.

04:37.111 --> 04:40.638
But I was just thinking you could tell me
about my mother instead.

04:40.748 --> 04:44.650
<i>All you ever said is she's from Virginia</i>
<i>and she's an only child like I am.</i>

04:44.752 --> 04:46.982
<i>I don't even know what</i>
<i>her favorite food was...</i>

04:47.087 --> 04:50.716
<i>and what she liked</i>
<i>to do and...nothin;</i>

04:58.666 --> 05:02.193
- You wanna know about your mama?
- Yeah.

05:03.304 --> 05:06.273
Mm-hmm.

05:06.373 --> 05:09.399
She used to spend hours
lurin' roaches and whatnot...

05:09.510 --> 05:12.206
out of the house with graham crackers
and marshmallows.

05:13.247 --> 05:15.909
Swear to God.

05:22.022 --> 05:24.013
She was a lunatic about savin' bugs.

05:39.106 --> 05:40.300
Here you go.

05:50.710 --> 05:54.669
<i>Hey, Lily! Nice ass!</i>

05:54.781 --> 05:56.749
Oh!

06:05.625 --> 06:07.593
Gotcha.

06:10.563 --> 06:14.294
Rosaleen.
Look at this thing fight.

06:14.400 --> 06:17.426
- What you doin' with that?
- Catching bees to show T. Ray.

06:17.537 --> 06:19.437
He thinks I'm making it up.

06:19.539 --> 06:22.201
Get yourself stung,
don't come cryin' to me.

06:22.308 --> 06:25.471
- Come fix this.
- For the future...

06:25.578 --> 06:27.159
What'd they do?
Drop the atom bomb or somethin'?

06:27.160 --> 06:28.741
Hush.

06:28.848 --> 06:33.046
It does say that there are those
who are equal before God...

06:33.152 --> 06:36.451
shall now also be equal
in the polling booths...

06:36.556 --> 06:38.888
in the classrooms,
in the factories...

06:38.992 --> 06:40.641
and in hotels and restaurants
and movie theaters...

06:40.642 --> 06:42.291
Holy shit.

06:42.395 --> 06:44.329
And other places that provide
service to the public.

06:44.430 --> 06:46.955
Today, July the 2nd, 1964...

06:47.066 --> 06:49.694
President Johnson signed
the Civil Rights bill into law.

07:09.322 --> 07:12.257
Fifteen, 16, 17, 18...

07:12.358 --> 07:15.486
19, 20, 21, 22.

08:31.070 --> 08:33.868
<i>When's my hair gonna</i>
<i>look like yours?</i>

08:35.642 --> 08:39.669
I bet mine used to drive you crazy the way
it goes off in 11 wrong directions.

08:41.414 --> 08:45.248
I bet you used to brush it a hundred times a day
just to get it to lay down.

08:47.387 --> 08:49.855
I bet you did.

08:50.923 --> 08:54.882
<i> Lily!</i>

08:54.994 --> 08:56.962
<i>Lily!</i>

08:58.631 --> 09:00.599
<i>Lily!</i>

09:05.705 --> 09:07.935
- Who you out here with?
- What?

09:08.041 --> 09:11.602
- Who's out there?
- Nobody. There's no one here but me. It's just me.

09:11.711 --> 09:13.645
Get up from there.

09:18.985 --> 09:21.351
Get in here.

09:21.454 --> 09:25.618
No! You think you're grown? Huh?

09:26.826 --> 09:29.818
Out there doing God knows what.

09:29.929 --> 09:33.160
You'll get yourself pregnant
and then what? Huh?

09:33.266 --> 09:35.291
Huh?

10:39.332 --> 10:41.300
You can go.

10:51.944 --> 10:54.879
Mornin'.

10:54.981 --> 10:57.609
How long your dad
keep you on these grits?

10:57.717 --> 10:59.685
Hour.

11:03.756 --> 11:05.747
Look at ya.

11:08.227 --> 11:10.354
Happy birthday.

11:11.664 --> 11:13.564
I didn't know you made me a cake.

11:13.666 --> 11:15.600
Of course I did.
It's your birthday.

11:15.701 --> 11:17.931
- How big a piece you want?
- Real big.

11:23.276 --> 11:25.676
You should be in the stand already.

11:25.778 --> 11:28.008
It's a big peach day.

11:32.185 --> 11:35.154
- Takin' her to town with me.
- What for?

11:35.254 --> 11:39.418
She needs a training bra.
She gots to get measured.

11:43.529 --> 11:45.520
How much something like that cost?

12:01.551 --> 12:03.815
Happy birthday.

12:10.927 --> 12:12.895
So what's in town anyway?

12:14.431 --> 12:17.025
I'm registerin' to vote.

12:17.134 --> 12:21.764
Rosaleen, news said a colored man in Mississippi
was killed for doing that.

12:22.906 --> 12:25.067
Good thing we ain't
in Mississippi then.

12:30.380 --> 12:33.474
I saw you scribblin' one of your stories
in the stand yesterday.

12:34.751 --> 12:36.776
Go on. Tell it.

12:36.887 --> 12:39.151
All right.

12:39.256 --> 12:41.315
So The Supremes,
they're heading down Highway 4...

12:41.424 --> 12:43.915
because they're going to Charleston
for a real big concert.

12:44.027 --> 12:45.927
But suddenly, their back tire blows up...

12:46.029 --> 12:48.259
and they go skiddin' across the road
and into a ditch.

12:48.365 --> 12:51.425
So then two are saying
that Diana's burnin' the peach cobbler.

12:51.535 --> 12:55.562
But she blocks the oven and she says, "I'm the
lead singer, and it's done when I say it's done."

12:55.672 --> 12:58.505
So I don't know what to do.
The Supremes are having a fight in my kitchen.

12:58.608 --> 13:01.509
- But then suddenly we hear...
- Hey.

13:01.611 --> 13:04.205
Ain't you Terence Ray's little girl?

13:04.314 --> 13:06.714
Yes, sir. Lily.

13:06.817 --> 13:09.718
<i>Daddy know you out here with her?</i>

13:09.820 --> 13:12.880
Rosaleen works for us.

13:12.989 --> 13:16.322
Whole lot of niggers been
coming through here today.

13:16.426 --> 13:18.986
You wouldn't be going to
that secret meetin', would ya?

13:19.095 --> 13:22.587
Well, hell, we ain't gotta
worry about this one.

13:22.699 --> 13:25.896
Can't register to vote
if you can't write your own name.

13:26.002 --> 13:30.371
Tell me, Lily. She a smart nigger
or a dumb nigger?

13:30.473 --> 13:32.168
- Please, mister, we really need...
- Answer me, girl.

13:39.115 --> 13:47.352
R-O-S-A-L-E-E-N.

13:49.092 --> 13:51.890
No!

13:53.163 --> 13:55.654
- Rosaleen! Stop!
- Put her there!

13:57.701 --> 14:00.329
Apologize!

14:00.437 --> 14:02.337
<i>Stop! No!</i>

14:02.439 --> 14:05.067
- Apologize!
- <i> Rosaleen, just apologize!</i>

14:06.309 --> 14:08.209
<i>Help! Somebody help!</i>

14:08.311 --> 14:10.211
Quiet.

14:10.313 --> 14:11.871
- Can somebody help?
- Apologize.

14:11.982 --> 14:13.745
Daddy!

14:17.320 --> 14:19.754
Your black ass gonna apologize
one way or the other.

14:24.661 --> 14:27.027
Rosaleen. Rosaleen.

14:32.202 --> 14:34.363
- Thank you, Sheriff.
- You have to help her.

14:34.471 --> 14:36.200
- <i> Get in the goddamn truck.</i>
- <i>I ain't restin;...</i>

14:36.306 --> 14:38.274
- till your nigger apologizes.
- I'm sorry, Frank!

14:38.375 --> 14:42.402
- I promised her!
- Get in the goddamn truck.

14:43.480 --> 14:46.449
She dumped snuff juice
on a white man...

14:46.549 --> 14:49.143
on Frank Posey, for Christ's sake.

14:49.252 --> 14:52.585
I wouldn't be surprised
if he flat-out kills her.

14:52.689 --> 14:57.456
You don't mean that.
He wouldn't really kill her.

14:57.560 --> 15:00.893
Sheriff s gonna take her to the hospital.
She'll be fine.

15:00.997 --> 15:03.488
Goddamn it. What the hell
were you thinkin'?

15:18.014 --> 15:20.312
Don't you leave this room, you hear?
I gotta settle payroll with...

15:20.417 --> 15:22.681
You don't scare me.

15:22.786 --> 15:25.254
- What'd you say?
- You're a coward.

15:27.254 --> 15:30.815
My mother would never let you touch me!

15:30.925 --> 15:33.519
That goddamn woman
give a shit about you.

15:33.628 --> 15:35.755
She loved me.

15:35.863 --> 15:38.161
I hate you!

15:47.608 --> 15:50.600
<i>Now you listen here.</i>

15:50.711 --> 15:55.546
Truth is, your sorry mama,
she ran off and left you.

15:57.385 --> 16:02.322
<i>On the day she died, she come back</i>
<i>for the rest of her things...not you.</i>

16:02.423 --> 16:04.288
That ain't true.

16:06.927 --> 16:09.327
It's not.

16:41.228 --> 16:43.628
<i>Dr. Cash, please call the page.</i>

16:43.731 --> 16:46.757
<i>Dr. Cash, please call</i>
<i>the page operator.</i>

16:57.178 --> 16:59.612
Rosaleen.

16:59.714 --> 17:01.511
They beat you again?

17:01.615 --> 17:04.948
We gotta get you out of here.

17:05.051 --> 17:08.419
- I can't get out of here. I'm in jail.
- You shouldn't be.

17:08.521 --> 17:10.990
That's gotta go.

17:17.263 --> 17:19.925
Rosaleen.

17:26.840 --> 17:30.208
- This is crazy.
- Oh, it'll be all right.

17:30.311 --> 17:32.108
It'll be all right.

17:38.052 --> 17:40.543
Shh.

17:55.836 --> 17:59.636
- A white girl come by here?
- Uh, no, sir. Nobody. I ain't moved from this spot.

18:22.096 --> 18:25.998
<i>When I was born</i>

18:26.100 --> 18:29.558
<i>My daddy said I was broken</i>

18:29.670 --> 18:32.639
<i>Beginning of the end</i>

18:32.740 --> 18:37.939
- You gals be careful now.
- <i>The life I hadn't chosen</i>

19:02.636 --> 19:04.797
Let me get this straight.

19:04.905 --> 19:07.135
You got us goin' to Tiburon...

19:07.241 --> 19:10.404
'cause your mama got a picture
with that town written on the back?

19:10.511 --> 19:12.536
That's it?

19:12.646 --> 19:14.910
T. Ray said my mother left me
way before she died.

19:19.687 --> 19:22.383
Well, it's not true.

19:22.489 --> 19:24.957
He only made it up to punish me.
I know he did.

19:25.059 --> 19:27.084
Knowing your daddy,
he could do a thing like that.

19:27.194 --> 19:29.856
And my mother could never do
what he said she did.

19:33.334 --> 19:35.234
Huh.

19:36.337 --> 19:38.396
I get it.

19:38.505 --> 19:40.530
You ran off 'cause of
what he said, didn't you?

19:41.976 --> 19:45.207
It ain't had nothin' to do
with me being in jail.

19:45.312 --> 19:50.375
And here you got me worrying myself sick
about you getting in trouble 'cause of me.

19:50.484 --> 19:54.750
So what you fixin' to do? Go door-to-door
askin' folks about your mama?

19:54.855 --> 19:57.346
- That's your bright idea?
- I don't exactly have a plan, all right?

19:57.458 --> 19:59.824
Well, you sure had one
back at the hospital.

19:59.927 --> 20:02.691
Comin' in there and sayin',
"We gonna do this, and we gonna do that."

20:02.796 --> 20:06.163
And I'm supposed to follow you
like some dumb nigger like they said.

20:06.267 --> 20:08.701
Well, you are dumb pouring your spit
on that man's shoe like that...

20:08.802 --> 20:11.600
and dumber not to say you're sorry
if sayin' it will save your life.

20:11.705 --> 20:13.798
That man was gonna come back
and kill you or worse.

20:13.908 --> 20:17.571
And I go and I get you out of there,
and this is how you thank me?

20:18.512 --> 20:21.003
Well, fine.

21:01.155 --> 21:03.055
Are you all right?

21:04.391 --> 21:06.484
I feel like I've been beaten
with a stick.

21:06.593 --> 21:08.857
You have been beaten, remember?

21:08.963 --> 21:11.761
But not with a stick.

21:20.541 --> 21:23.169
I know you can't understand.

21:23.277 --> 21:27.680
Apologizing to those men
would've just been a different way of dyin'...

21:27.781 --> 21:30.011
'cept I have to live with it.

21:33.954 --> 21:37.856
If I can find someplace open,
I'll buy us some food.

21:37.958 --> 21:40.119
What we gonna do for beds?

21:40.227 --> 21:42.559
Find a motel, I guess.

21:42.663 --> 21:45.757
Lily, there ain't gonna be a place
that'll take a colored woman.

21:45.866 --> 21:47.857
Well, what about
the Civil Rights Act?

21:50.004 --> 21:52.495
Ain't nothin' but a piece of paper.

22:02.616 --> 22:05.949
Excuse me, sir.
Are you serving food today?

22:06.053 --> 22:09.887
Oh, yes, ma'am. We have
a Sunday plate special: Barbecued pork.

22:09.990 --> 22:12.481
Um, we'll take two of those,
please, and two Cokes.

22:15.295 --> 22:16.887
I don't believe
I've seen you before.

22:16.997 --> 22:19.932
I'm not from here.
I'm... I'm just visiting my grandmother.

22:20.034 --> 22:22.366
<i>Your daddy's gonna be so proud of you.</i>

22:22.469 --> 22:24.266
- Afternoon, Carol.
- Hi.

22:24.371 --> 22:25.838
- Why, don't you two look smart.
- When we get home...

22:25.939 --> 22:29.272
You come on in, and I'll wrap
those up for you to go.

22:43.357 --> 22:45.985
Miss, you change your mind?

22:46.093 --> 22:49.426
- Where did you get those?
- Oh, I know what you mean.

22:49.530 --> 22:52.055
<i>Virgin Mary's pictured</i>
<i>as a colored woman.</i>

22:52.166 --> 22:55.135
<i>But, see, the woman that makes</i>
<i>the honey is colored herself.</i>

22:55.235 --> 22:57.533
Best honey in South Carolina.

22:57.638 --> 22:59.299
What is her name?

22:59.406 --> 23:02.204
August Boatwright.

23:02.309 --> 23:04.402
Do you know where she lives?

23:04.511 --> 23:09.107
Darnedest house you ever saw. Painted like
Pepto-Bismol. Your grandma's probably seen it.

23:15.122 --> 23:16.953
<i>What do you think's goin' on?</i>

23:17.057 --> 23:20.493
Look like they dressed for church.

23:20.594 --> 23:23.154
- Bye-bye!
- <i> You think one of them's August?</i>

23:23.263 --> 23:25.288
Whoever she is, I hope she make honey...

23:25.399 --> 23:27.560
better than she picks out paint.

23:28.602 --> 23:30.832
I like it.

23:50.390 --> 23:53.325
Now, don't go gettin'
your hopes up, all right?

23:53.427 --> 23:55.691
They got nowhere else to go.

24:13.280 --> 24:15.043
Yes?

24:15.149 --> 24:18.380
- Are you August Boatwright?
- <i>No.</i>

24:18.485 --> 24:22.444
I'm June Boatwright.
August is my sister.

24:23.657 --> 24:27.525
- You came to see her?
- Hi. I'm May Boatwright.

24:27.628 --> 24:31.086
I'm August's sister too.

24:31.198 --> 24:33.462
Is she expecting you?

24:33.567 --> 24:35.865
Um, I just saw some honey at the store,
and the man said that...

24:35.969 --> 24:37.960
You come for honey?

24:38.071 --> 24:42.371
Why didn't you say so?
Come into the parlor. I'll go get her.

24:42.476 --> 24:45.968
Then after that she gonna go get
September and October.

25:26.620 --> 25:28.520
<i>Who we got here?</i>

25:32.059 --> 25:34.687
I'm Lily and this is Rosaleen.

25:36.863 --> 25:39.423
We need a place to stay.

25:43.136 --> 25:46.469
You see, my mother died of tularemia when
I was little, and my daddy just got killed...

25:46.573 --> 25:49.633
in a tractor accident on our farm in
Spartanburg County, so me and Rosaleen...

25:49.743 --> 25:52.769
she's our housekeeper... we're on our way
to Virginia to stay with my Aunt Bernie.

25:52.879 --> 25:55.211
'Cept I don't have money
for a train ticket or a motel...

25:55.315 --> 25:57.340
and not that anyone
would take in a Negro woman...

25:57.451 --> 25:59.681
even though it's a violation
of the Civil Rights Act.

26:07.494 --> 26:11.555
- Looks like you've been beaten.
- She fell down some steps when we were leavin'.

26:11.665 --> 26:14.327
Must've been a lot of steps.

26:34.288 --> 26:37.655
May, honey, go on out to the wall
and finish your crying.

26:43.230 --> 26:45.425
Is she all right?

26:45.532 --> 26:47.864
I'm sorry.
We can't help you.

26:49.269 --> 26:52.500
We can't have 'em living
on the side of the road.

26:52.606 --> 26:56.042
Why don't you call your aunt,
see about her sending you some train fare?

26:56.143 --> 27:01.979
I would, but she just had a real big operation
and she's still stayin' in the hospital.

27:02.082 --> 27:06.451
<i>So maybe Rosaleen and I could just work</i>
<i>for the money, and then just be on our way.</i>

27:10.057 --> 27:12.525
Well...

27:12.626 --> 27:15.891
I guess Rosaleen can help
May in the kitchen...

27:15.996 --> 27:18.021
and you can help me and Zach
with the bees.

27:18.131 --> 27:20.463
August.

27:20.567 --> 27:22.899
We have the cots in the honey house.

27:26.239 --> 27:29.970
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

27:32.946 --> 27:34.937
<i>I hope y'all like the smell of honey.</i>

27:35.048 --> 27:36.948
<i>It can be a bit overwhelming at first...</i>

27:37.050 --> 27:39.018
<i>but you'll get used to it.</i>

27:39.119 --> 27:43.749
Zach and I sleep out here come in December
when we harvestin' honey round the clock.

27:45.158 --> 27:48.855
It can get hot out here,
so you wanna keep that on.

27:48.962 --> 27:50.862
You'll have to use
the bathroom in the house.

27:50.964 --> 27:54.695
We never lock the door, so just come on in
whenever you need to.

27:54.801 --> 27:58.202
- There you go.
- This ain't charity. I'll pay you back for it.

27:58.305 --> 28:00.739
Oh, yeah, you can work it off.

28:00.841 --> 28:03.810
I imagine y'all two wanna rest up.

28:03.910 --> 28:09.678
If you get hungry, there's some sweet potato
biscuits on the stove. They're May's specialty.

28:09.783 --> 28:11.410
Thank you again, Miss August.

28:19.326 --> 28:23.353
I'm sure sorry to hear about T. Ray.
Aunt Bernie too.

28:23.463 --> 28:25.522
I know it wasn't right to lie,
but I didn't have a choice.

28:25.632 --> 28:28.226
How come you ain't say nothin'
about your mama or show that picture?

28:28.335 --> 28:30.235
Ain't that why we're here
in the first place?

28:30.337 --> 28:33.135
If they knew I ran away,
they'd have to call T. Ray to come get me.

28:33.240 --> 28:36.835
Then they'd find out you a fugitive
and they'd have to call the police.

28:36.943 --> 28:41.573
I feel like I'm where I'm supposed to be.
I really do.

28:41.681 --> 28:46.482
I just need some time to figure out why,
