50:11.346 --> 50:13.371
<i>June, what's gotten into you?</i>

50:14.248 --> 50:17.775
Oh!

50:17.885 --> 50:19.876
Lily.

50:23.791 --> 50:25.759
Girl, since when
you started faintin'?

50:29.263 --> 50:31.163
Could I get some water?

50:32.266 --> 50:35.531
- Of course.
- Wait. Um...

50:35.636 --> 50:37.729
Rosaleen, could you get it, please?

50:52.820 --> 50:54.788
This your room?

50:56.290 --> 51:00.727
- Blue is my favorite color.
- Mine too.

51:00.828 --> 51:03.388
Birds of a feather.

51:03.498 --> 51:07.298
- Sorry I messed up your church.
- Oh, that's all right.

51:07.402 --> 51:10.769
We go on all day if somebody
don't stop us.

51:10.872 --> 51:12.772
I just hope you all right.

51:18.379 --> 51:20.279
I think it was the heat.

51:21.449 --> 51:23.815
<i>Felt like it was</i>
<i>90 degrees in there.</i>

51:27.855 --> 51:30.483
Yes, the heat.

51:32.293 --> 51:35.751
Heat'll make a person
do strange things.

52:03.509 --> 52:07.946
I've made my reservation
I'm leaving town tomorrow

52:08.047 --> 52:10.248
I'll find somebody new
and there'll be no more sorrow

52:12.551 --> 52:15.019
That's what I do each time
but I can't follow through

52:15.120 --> 52:19.420
I can't break away
though you make me cry

52:19.525 --> 52:23.928
I can't break away
I can't say good-bye

52:24.029 --> 52:27.726
No, I'll never, ever
break away from you

52:27.833 --> 52:31.360
No, no
No, no, no, no

52:31.470 --> 52:33.665
No, no, no, no
No, no, no, no

52:33.772 --> 52:36.639
Who can think with all that?

52:36.742 --> 52:41.577
<i>Well, that's your problem...</i>
<i>You think too much.</i>

52:41.680 --> 52:45.343
Try going with your feelings
once in a blue moon.

52:45.451 --> 52:47.419
You won't believe what
people in town are sayin'.

52:47.519 --> 52:51.683
Sayin' Jack Palance is coming to Tiburon,
and he's bringing a Negro woman with him.

52:51.790 --> 52:53.451
<i>What in the world?</i>

52:53.559 --> 52:57.086
- Who's Jack Palance?
- He's a movie star... a white one.

52:57.196 --> 53:00.597
I ain't never heard...
l... I have never heard of him.

53:00.699 --> 53:02.894
<i>They say his sister lives here.</i>
<i>He's comin' to visit her...</i>

53:03.002 --> 53:05.368
and he intend to take this woman
to the theater on Friday.

53:05.471 --> 53:09.373
- <i>White folks talkin' about standin' guard outside.</i>
- <i> That's just talk.</i>

53:09.475 --> 53:11.272
<i>And these idiots are determined</i>
<i>to fight this law till they...</i>

53:11.377 --> 53:12.867
Shh, shh, shh. Shh.

53:16.448 --> 53:17.915
- Miss May?
- Mm-hmm?

53:18.017 --> 53:21.077
I saw how nice you did
Rosaleen's hair...

53:21.186 --> 53:24.087
and I was wonderin' if maybe
you could help me with mine.

53:26.191 --> 53:27.806
That'll be easy.

53:29.374 --> 53:31.274
<i>Hmm.</i>

53:37.761 --> 53:40.821
It's ironic how white people
hate us so much...

53:40.931 --> 53:43.297
when so many of 'em
been raised by black women.

53:45.235 --> 53:47.897
- Place a beehive on my grave
- Ooh.

53:49.239 --> 53:52.970
June Bug! June, I know you hear me.

53:53.076 --> 53:55.840
If I make this shot, you'll give me your hand?
Watch this.

54:00.984 --> 54:02.975
<i>What you laughin' at?</i>

54:08.792 --> 54:12.023
You think somethin' bein' an impossibility
makes you think about it even more?

54:12.128 --> 54:14.596
- Like what?
- I don't know.

54:14.698 --> 54:17.223
Like... kissin'.

54:17.334 --> 54:19.962
That ain't impossible.

54:20.070 --> 54:24.063
When I was 15, I made
a 7 UP cake for this boy.

54:24.174 --> 54:26.904
After that,
he kissed me all the time.

54:27.010 --> 54:29.103
What'd it feel like?

54:29.212 --> 54:31.373
Like I was gonna burst.

54:36.186 --> 54:39.019
Miss May, I know you get
real sad sometimes.

54:40.056 --> 54:43.150
My daddy never feels.

54:43.260 --> 54:46.058
He never felt anything.

54:46.162 --> 54:48.596
I had rather be like you.

54:53.570 --> 54:56.232
A worker bee weigh less
than a flower petal...

54:56.339 --> 55:00.901
but she can fly with a load
heavier than her.

55:01.011 --> 55:04.572
But she only lives
four or five weeks.

55:06.283 --> 55:10.652
Sometimes not feelin' is
the only way you can survive.

55:19.829 --> 55:22.457
You want me to help you
make a 7 UP cake?

55:24.134 --> 55:27.126
Hold that.

55:40.717 --> 55:43.515
- It's purple.
- Yeah.

55:43.620 --> 55:47.351
When the weather turns hot,
the flowers, they start to dry up.

55:47.457 --> 55:49.925
The bees, they start sucking
on that elderberry.

55:50.961 --> 55:52.986
That makes purple honey.

55:54.130 --> 55:57.122
There. See?

55:57.233 --> 56:01.135
People'll pay two dollars a jar
for purple honey.

56:50.086 --> 56:51.986
- <i> I'm so lonely</i>
- You all right?

56:52.088 --> 56:54.147
<i> She'll be fine.</i>

56:56.359 --> 56:58.190
- <i> Because.</i>
- <i> No. Why?</i>

56:58.294 --> 57:00.990
- Why does it always have to come back to this?
- Because I love you and you me.

57:01.097 --> 57:02.797
Neil, I don't wanna get married.
I don't wanna get married.

57:02.798 --> 57:04.498
That's what people in love do.

57:04.601 --> 57:05.835
I don't wanna be married today
or tomorrow or ever.

57:05.836 --> 57:07.069
It's about that time!

57:07.170 --> 57:09.570
- What are you so scared of?
- I'm not scared of anything!

57:13.209 --> 57:15.575
Then you are the most
selfish bitch I ever met.

57:19.182 --> 57:21.082
What?

57:21.184 --> 57:23.084
What did you just say to me?

57:23.186 --> 57:25.450
- Oh, Lord.
- <i>What did you just call me?</i>

57:25.555 --> 57:28.251
<i>How dare you call me that, Neil.</i>
<i>Neil, I'm talkin' to you.</i>

57:28.358 --> 57:30.918
You better turn around
and listen to me right now.

57:31.027 --> 57:33.052
You better come back here
and apologize right now!

57:33.163 --> 57:36.599
<i>Don't you ever plan on comin' back then!</i>
<i>I don't even need you in my life!</i>

57:37.801 --> 57:40.861
How dare... Don't come back!

57:40.970 --> 57:43.962
- <i> Don't worry, May.</i>
- <i> Don't come back!</i>

57:49.045 --> 57:51.912
<i> I bet they'll be back holdin' hands</i>
<i>on the porch swing tomorrow.</i>

57:52.015 --> 57:56.714
I don't know, Lily.
Some people rather die than forgive.

57:56.820 --> 57:58.981
And June is one of 'em.

57:59.089 --> 58:03.355
She still hasn't forgiven me for paintin'
the house, and that was 10 years ago.

58:03.460 --> 58:06.952
Well, how come, if your favorite color is blue,
you painted the house so pink?

58:07.063 --> 58:09.395
That was May's doin'.

58:09.499 --> 58:11.899
She was with me the day
I went to the paint store...

58:12.001 --> 58:15.903
and she latched onto this sample
called Caribbean Pink.

58:16.005 --> 58:19.998
Said it made her wanna dance
a Spanish flamenco.

58:20.110 --> 58:23.705
I thought it was the tackiest color
I ever seen in my life.

58:23.813 --> 58:27.681
But if it could lift May's heart,
then I guess she ought to live in it.

58:27.784 --> 58:29.752
Well, that was sure nice of you.

58:29.853 --> 58:33.380
Well, some things
don't matter that much, Lily.

58:33.490 --> 58:36.357
Like the color
of a house and whatnot.

58:36.459 --> 58:39.087
But liftin' someone's heart...
now <i>that</i> matters.

58:40.597 --> 58:44.124
- Were you ever in love?
- Course I was.

58:44.234 --> 58:47.169
- But you didn't love him enough to marry him.
- Well, I loved him enough.

58:47.270 --> 58:50.433
I just loved my freedom more.

58:50.540 --> 58:55.136
I can't think of one thing I'd rather have
than somebody loving me.

58:59.315 --> 59:00.805
Where are all the bees?

59:05.800 --> 59:08.667
You hear that?

59:08.769 --> 59:10.964
They're coolin' the hive.

59:11.072 --> 59:15.008
That's the sound of 100,000
bee wings fannin' the air.

59:18.145 --> 59:22.605
People have no idea about the complicated life
goin' on inside a beehive.

59:22.717 --> 59:24.981
Here. Let me help you with that.

59:25.086 --> 59:29.955
See, bees have a secret life
we don't know anything about.

59:41.235 --> 59:43.169
<i>Yeah!</i>

59:44.505 --> 59:47.065
<i>Well, if this ain't the livin' end.</i>

59:47.174 --> 59:48.835
Now come over here. You gonna get wet.

59:48.943 --> 59:52.071
Oh, Lord, Lord!

59:54.949 --> 59:59.386
Would you keep it down?

59:59.487 --> 01:00:03.184
- Keep it down! I'm practicin'.
- You come over here, you gonna get wet.

01:00:05.026 --> 01:00:07.654
- Oh, damn it to hell!
- Run, Lily!

01:00:07.762 --> 01:00:09.730
Oh, damn it to hell!

01:00:12.099 --> 01:00:14.693
How dare you!

01:00:14.802 --> 01:00:17.327
- <i> You out of your mind?</i>
- All right now, June.

01:00:20.341 --> 01:00:22.502
<i>Come on, June.</i>

01:01:24.405 --> 01:01:26.669
- Where you goin', June?
- June?

01:01:26.774 --> 01:01:29.208
Come on back.

01:01:36.183 --> 01:01:38.913
<i>Oh. Miss May.</i>

01:01:39.019 --> 01:01:41.954
Got thirsty.

01:01:59.733 --> 01:02:02.167
I saw a roach.

01:02:20.620 --> 01:02:25.148
<i>The roaches will</i>
<i>follow this right out the door.</i>

01:02:25.258 --> 01:02:27.522
Works every time.

01:02:30.764 --> 01:02:33.528
Miss May?

01:02:33.633 --> 01:02:35.897
Did you know a Deborah?

01:02:36.002 --> 01:02:37.902
Deborah Owens?

01:02:38.004 --> 01:02:41.405
<i>She's a white woman from Virginia.</i>

01:02:42.542 --> 01:02:45.306
It would've been a long time ago.

01:02:45.412 --> 01:02:47.676
Oh, yes.

01:02:47.781 --> 01:02:50.147
Deborah Owens.

01:02:50.250 --> 01:02:53.083
She stayed out in the honey house.

01:02:53.186 --> 01:02:56.417
She was the sweetest thing.

01:03:12.372 --> 01:03:15.170
Think I'll go out
to the wall for a while.

01:03:34.361 --> 01:03:37.262
Give it back!

01:03:42.936 --> 01:03:45.370
<i>Zach! Come back here.</i>

01:03:51.211 --> 01:03:53.111
Thank you.

01:03:56.583 --> 01:03:59.347
<i>Hey. Lily, come ride with me.</i>

01:03:59.452 --> 01:04:02.649
Uh, I gotta drop some honey off
to Mr. Forrest. I want you to meet him.

01:04:02.756 --> 01:04:05.156
Oh, I gotta talk to Miss August.
You know where she is?

01:04:05.258 --> 01:04:09.251
Uh, she went to Columbia to go pick up
a new blade for the spinner.

01:04:09.362 --> 01:04:11.262
Oh.

01:04:22.675 --> 01:04:27.112
<i>Thought a new notebook might</i>
<i>help you start writin' again.</i>

01:04:29.916 --> 01:04:31.816
Whoa.

01:04:39.526 --> 01:04:42.324
My mother stayed in
the honey house, just like me.

01:04:42.429 --> 01:04:45.626
What? When?

01:04:45.732 --> 01:04:48.929
I don't know.
I don't know anything about her.

01:04:49.035 --> 01:04:53.631
Maybe it was before I was born.
Or maybe she left me like my daddy said.

01:04:53.740 --> 01:04:55.640
So, wait.

01:04:57.410 --> 01:04:59.640
You mean to tell me...

01:04:59.746 --> 01:05:02.180
all that stuff about your aunt...

01:05:02.282 --> 01:05:04.876
and... and just passin' through...

01:05:04.984 --> 01:05:07.282
You made that up?

01:05:09.022 --> 01:05:11.286
Why not just tell the truth?

01:05:12.826 --> 01:05:15.192
'Cause I'm afraid the truth
is gonna wreck everything.

01:05:39.986 --> 01:05:41.886
<i>There he is.</i>

01:05:41.988 --> 01:05:43.819
And who might
this pretty young lady be?

01:05:43.923 --> 01:05:47.017
This is Lily.
She's stayin' with Miss August.

01:05:47.126 --> 01:05:50.323
- You stayin' in her house?
- Yes, ma'am.

01:05:50.430 --> 01:05:54.730
Well, Miss August is a good friend of mine.
I hope you're enjoyin' yourself.

01:05:54.834 --> 01:05:57.667
- Yes, sir.
- I have an appointment with the dentist.

01:05:57.770 --> 01:05:59.567
Okay.

01:05:59.672 --> 01:06:04.075
- <i> What you working on?</i>
- <i>Run-of-the-mill stuff.</i>

01:06:04.177 --> 01:06:07.578
<i>Hey, I got somethin' for you.</i>
<i>Wanna head up to the office?</i>

01:06:07.680 --> 01:06:10.410
Are you, uh, lookin' forward
to school gettin' started up?

01:06:10.411 --> 01:06:13.141
Yes, sir. And football season...

01:06:13.253 --> 01:06:15.483
Oh, yeah.
We're lookin' forward to that.

01:06:49.556 --> 01:06:51.456
Hello. Operator.

01:06:51.558 --> 01:06:54.925
I'd like to make a call
to Sylvan 7-1710.

01:06:55.028 --> 01:06:57.963
Hold while I connect
your call, please.

01:07:02.368 --> 01:07:05.394
Hello? Hello!

01:07:10.910 --> 01:07:14.676
Look what he gave me.
I'm startin' my law library.

01:07:14.781 --> 01:07:16.942
That's nice.

01:07:17.050 --> 01:07:18.950
Hey.

01:07:21.921 --> 01:07:25.152
Lily, I know you're scared
the truth is gonna wreck things.

01:07:25.258 --> 01:07:27.988
Findin' out the truth
is only half of it.

01:07:29.195 --> 01:07:32.028
It's what you do with it
that matters.

01:07:32.131 --> 01:07:34.031
Right?

01:07:41.474 --> 01:07:43.806
When's the last time
you seen a movie?

01:07:43.910 --> 01:07:45.810
I don't remember.

01:07:45.912 --> 01:07:48.039
Come on. We gonna go see <i>Surf Party.</i>

01:07:48.147 --> 01:07:51.605
- But what...
- But nothin'. Come on. Let's go.

01:08:00.126 --> 01:08:01.923
- One adult, please.
- Here you go.

01:08:03.771 --> 01:08:04.863
It can't hurt, you know?

01:08:08.843 --> 01:08:10.834
<i>One adult and one child.</i>

01:08:13.314 --> 01:08:15.544
<i>Everybody waxed up?</i>

01:08:15.649 --> 01:08:19.415
- <i>This is a surfboard.</i>
- <i> You're kidding.</i>

01:08:19.520 --> 01:08:22.978
<i>This is the nose.</i>
<i>The sides are called rails.</i>

01:08:24.692 --> 01:08:26.660
Thank you.

01:08:29.763 --> 01:08:32.129
- <i>The first step</i> is...
- <i> Come on!</i>

01:08:32.933 --> 01:08:35.367
Hey, boy!

01:08:35.469 --> 01:08:38.029
- We're gonna teach you a lesson, boy!
- Hey! It's not his fault!

01:08:38.139 --> 01:08:39.868
Let him go!

01:08:39.974 --> 01:08:42.738
Shut your mouth, nigger lover!

01:08:42.843 --> 01:08:46.870
- <i> Where are they takin' him?</i>
- Get him in the truck.

01:08:46.981 --> 01:08:49.745
- Just trying to gather up all the pieces.
- You're wastin' time!

01:08:49.850 --> 01:08:51.750
- You know who took him.
- Is that right?

01:08:51.852 --> 01:08:54.319
- <i>Yeah, that's right.</i>
- All right. Now hold on here, folks.

01:08:54.421 --> 01:08:56.854
<i>Soon as we know anything,</i>
<i>we'll get back to you.</i>

01:08:56.957 --> 01:08:59.687
Neil, counselor, ladies.
Come on. Let's go.

01:09:02.630 --> 01:09:06.066
I'm gonna get some men together.
We'll look ourselves.

01:09:06.167 --> 01:09:08.828
If you'll have me,
I'm willin' to help.

01:09:16.343 --> 01:09:18.368
May doesn't need to know about this.

01:09:23.184 --> 01:09:25.913
Nah, it'll be too much.

01:09:32.560 --> 01:09:35.620
<i>Black boys don't come back, August.</i>

01:09:35.729 --> 01:09:39.130
<i> He's gonna be found,</i>
<i>and he's gonna be all right.</i>

01:09:39.233 --> 01:09:41.929
- <i> How could you say that?</i>
- <i>I have to.</i>

01:09:59.720 --> 01:10:02.985
Please let him be okay.

01:10:23.444 --> 01:10:25.435
Lily's gonna look so pretty in this.

01:10:31.252 --> 01:10:33.982
August, where are your scissors?

01:10:35.689 --> 01:10:37.486
Uh, in my room.

01:10:50.337 --> 01:10:54.000
- <i>Hey, Greta.</i>
- Hey, May.

01:10:54.108 --> 01:10:56.008
You been to see Mary?

01:10:57.044 --> 01:10:58.978
Zach is still missin'.

01:11:03.784 --> 01:11:06.981
We have to pray, May.
You understand?

01:11:07.087 --> 01:11:09.282
We got to pray, May.

01:11:35.149 --> 01:11:38.550
- <i> Who was at the door?</i>
- <i>May, was somebody at the door?</i>

01:11:41.722 --> 01:11:43.622
Greta.

01:11:44.892 --> 01:11:47.292
No news on Zach.

01:11:56.437 --> 01:11:58.905
Why didn't you tell me?

01:12:00.741 --> 01:12:03.539
You all right?

01:12:05.779 --> 01:12:08.247
May?

01:12:08.349 --> 01:12:10.442
May!

01:12:11.552 --> 01:12:13.179
<i>Answer me, May.</i>
<i>You all right?</i>

01:12:13.287 --> 01:12:15.755
What's happened to her?
I never seen her like this.

01:12:15.856 --> 01:12:19.656
- May?
- May?

01:12:19.760 --> 01:12:21.660
May.

01:12:23.797 --> 01:12:25.788
I'm all right.

01:12:28.068 --> 01:12:30.195
Glad to see you can talk.

01:12:31.739 --> 01:12:34.071
Come on, Sister.

01:12:34.174 --> 01:12:36.506
We gonna run you a nice hot bath.

01:12:37.878 --> 01:12:40.438
I need to go to the wall.

01:12:51.291 --> 01:12:53.191
May?

01:12:53.293 --> 01:12:55.727
Where's May?
Her bath is ready.

01:12:55.829 --> 01:12:57.990
She's still out there.

01:13:04.605 --> 01:13:06.664
May?

01:13:08.075 --> 01:13:09.975
May?

01:13:11.545 --> 01:13:13.445
May!

01:13:16.650 --> 01:13:18.675
May?

01:13:19.820 --> 01:13:22.015
<i>May!</i>

01:13:22.122 --> 01:13:24.420
- May?
- <i>May!</i>

01:13:26.293 --> 01:13:28.784
- May?
- <i>May!</i>

01:13:31.365 --> 01:13:33.856
<i>Come on, May.</i>

01:13:40.774 --> 01:13:42.674
<i>May?</i>

01:13:46.480 --> 01:13:48.380
<i>May?</i>

01:13:51.585 --> 01:13:53.485
June?

01:13:56.156 --> 01:13:58.454
<i>May!</i>

01:14:05.332 --> 01:14:10.031
<i>June! June!</i>

01:14:10.137 --> 01:14:12.799
May!

01:14:12.906 --> 01:14:16.239
- Oh, my God.
- Oh, my God! August!

01:14:19.346 --> 01:14:21.541
August.

01:14:32.626 --> 01:14:37.063
No!
Oh, no!

01:14:37.164 --> 01:14:40.327
- Oh, no!
- Oh, May.

01:14:43.270 --> 01:14:46.671
<i> We gotta get her out.</i>
<i>We gotta get her out.</i>

01:14:54.147 --> 01:14:59.050
<i>May!</i>

01:14:59.152 --> 01:15:01.313
Why you do that?

01:16:06.553 --> 01:16:08.919
Sweet Mary.

01:16:16.496 --> 01:16:18.964
<i>Zach!</i>

01:16:20.934 --> 01:16:23.095
Zach.

01:16:27.074 --> 01:16:29.599
<i>Oh.</i>

01:16:29.710 --> 01:16:31.610
I'm so sorry.

01:16:31.712 --> 01:16:33.771
Miss May did what she did
'cause of me.

01:16:33.880 --> 01:16:36.474
<i>Come on, now.</i>
<i>It was May who did it.</i>

01:16:36.583 --> 01:16:39.984
It's all right.
She wouldn't want you blaming yourself.

01:16:44.191 --> 01:16:46.489
Oh. It's gonna be okay.

01:16:49.696 --> 01:16:51.755
It's good. It's good.

01:17:20.127 --> 01:17:23.619
<i>Dear August and June...</i>

01:17:23.730 --> 01:17:26.858
<i>I'm sorry to leave you like this.</i>

01:17:26.967 --> 01:17:29.595
<i>But I know Zach is okay.</i>

01:17:29.703 --> 01:17:32.570
<i>My heart is telling me so.</i>

01:17:32.673 --> 01:17:34.573
<i>I hate you bein'sad...</i>

01:17:34.675 --> 01:17:38.736
<i>but think how happy I'll be</i>
<i>with April, Mama and Papa.</i>

01:17:40.080 --> 01:17:42.947
<i>I'm tired of carrying around</i>
<i>the weight of the world.</i>

01:17:43.050 --> 01:17:45.109
<i>I'm just gonna lay it down now.</i>

01:17:46.753 --> 01:17:48.653
<i>It's my time to die...</i>

01:17:48.755 --> 01:17:51.451
<i>and it's your time to live.</i>

01:17:51.558 --> 01:17:54.686
<i>Don't mess it up.</i>

01:17:55.896 --> 01:17:57.454
<i>Love, May.</i>

01:18:10.677 --> 01:18:12.577
<i>I saw Mary</i>

01:18:12.679 --> 01:18:15.842
<i>She was walkin' on the water</i>

01:18:15.949 --> 01:18:18.611
<i>Smilin' at me</i>

01:18:18.719 --> 01:18:22.917
<i>Hummin' her river song</i>

01:18:23.023 --> 01:18:24.923
<i>And I tried wavin'</i>

01:18:25.025 --> 01:18:27.755
<i>But she was walkin' away</i>

01:18:27.861 --> 01:18:31.524
<i>She said that</i>
<i>she'd been waitin' on me</i>

01:18:31.631 --> 01:18:35.294
<i>All day long</i>

01:18:46.913 --> 01:18:51.612
<i>I tried to call her and said</i>
<i>Please come back</i>

01:18:51.718 --> 01:18:57.088
<i>'Cause I didn't mean</i>
<i>to make you sad</i>

01:18:57.190 --> 01:18:59.090
<i>She said</i>

01:18:59.192 --> 01:19:03.526
<i>Well, don't you worry</i>
<i>'cause I'll see you again</i>

01:19:03.630 --> 01:19:06.656
<i>But I hear my mother call</i>

01:19:06.767 --> 01:19:09.736
<i>And I have to go</i>

01:20:04.191 --> 01:20:09.356
Place a beehive on my grave

01:20:09.462 --> 01:20:13.057
And let the honey
soak through

01:20:14.501 --> 01:20:18.369
When I'm dead and gone

01:20:18.471 --> 01:20:23.101
That's what I want from you

01:20:23.210 --> 01:20:28.170
The streets of heaven
are gold and sunny

01:20:28.281 --> 01:20:31.011
But I'll stick with my plot

01:20:31.117 --> 01:20:34.484
And a pot of honey

01:20:34.588 --> 01:20:39.150
Place a beehive on my grave

01:20:39.259 --> 01:20:43.252
And let the honey
soak through

01:20:46.533 --> 01:20:48.433
Hmm.

01:20:53.740 --> 01:20:55.640
<i>I see you liked yours.</i>

01:20:55.742 --> 01:20:57.573
- Mm-hmm. It's the last one.
- Mmm.

01:20:57.677 --> 01:20:59.736
Mmm, girl, you did all right.

01:20:59.846 --> 01:21:02.371
Aw. I'm the eldest.

01:21:02.482 --> 01:21:05.246
- And the slowest.
- I'll make some more.

01:21:05.352 --> 01:21:08.412
- You hear that, June?
- Hmm.

01:21:08.521 --> 01:21:12.252
Think we might need
to change your name, Rosaleen.

01:21:12.359 --> 01:21:16.056
From now on, we gonna call you July.

01:21:18.265 --> 01:21:21.428
<i>Hmm. I concur.</i>

01:21:23.203 --> 01:21:25.569
<i>Some more of these.</i>

01:21:27.040 --> 01:21:30.134
<i>Mmm.</i>

01:21:35.115 --> 01:21:37.777
Sure you gonna be
all right in here by yourself?

01:21:43.290 --> 01:21:45.588
I don't mind sharing May's room.

01:21:45.692 --> 01:21:48.593
Just wanna be near her spirit.

01:21:48.695 --> 01:21:50.595
I'll be fine.

01:21:52.799 --> 01:21:54.699
See you in the mornin' then.

01:22:24.898 --> 01:22:26.798
Hey, Lily.

01:22:27.901 --> 01:22:30.199
This is my mother.

01:22:37.911 --> 01:22:39.811
I know, honey.

01:22:41.214 --> 01:22:45.048
Your mama was
Deborah Fontanel Owens.

01:22:45.151 --> 01:22:47.051
You've known all this time?

01:22:47.153 --> 01:22:50.987
I knew she had a daughter.
But I thought it couldn't be you.

01:22:51.091 --> 01:22:55.858
But one look at you,
all I could see is Deborah at your age.

01:22:55.962 --> 01:22:57.759
You knew her when she was little?

01:22:57.864 --> 01:23:00.833
I took care of her.

01:23:00.934 --> 01:23:03.596
Why didn't you tell me?

01:23:03.703 --> 01:23:07.036
Somethin' told me you wasn't
quite ready to know about her.

01:23:07.140 --> 01:23:12.043
I just wanted to give you a chance
to get on solid ground first.

01:23:14.647 --> 01:23:16.808
T. Ray...

01:23:16.916 --> 01:23:18.941
he told me that my mo...

01:23:20.253 --> 01:23:23.450
He told me my mother
left me and ran away.

01:23:26.259 --> 01:23:29.490
I don't have any memory of her, but...

01:23:29.596 --> 01:23:33.896
I know he's lyin'
'cause some things aren't possible.

01:23:34.000 --> 01:23:36.560
Children just don't have two parents
who refuse to love 'em.

01:23:36.669 --> 01:23:40.127
Is that what made you leave?

01:23:40.240 --> 01:23:44.438
I know what I did was wrong.
I just seem to do all the wrong things.

01:23:46.146 --> 01:23:49.274
I don't mean to be a bad person,
but I just can't help it.

01:23:49.382 --> 01:23:53.580
So that's why I gotta go.
I brought the outside in here.

01:23:53.686 --> 01:23:56.814
And what happened
to Zach and Miss May...

01:23:56.923 --> 01:23:59.949
If I'd never come here,
it would've never happened.

01:24:00.060 --> 01:24:02.153
- Lily... Lily, that wasn't your fault.
- I wreck everything.

01:24:02.262 --> 01:24:04.321
Yes, it was.

01:24:04.431 --> 01:24:08.231
They were fightin' and screamin' and...

01:24:08.334 --> 01:24:12.065
She grabbed a gun, and he took it away from her,
and I just wanted to help her.

01:24:12.172 --> 01:24:14.868
I just wanted to
give it back to her.

01:24:14.974 --> 01:24:17.238
- And I killed her.
- Who, Lily?

01:24:17.343 --> 01:24:20.642
My mother.
I killed my mother.

01:24:22.382 --> 01:24:25.010
I'm unlovable.

01:24:31.191 --> 01:24:33.318
Oh, Lily.

01:24:34.594 --> 01:24:36.494
You listen to me now.

01:24:39.566 --> 01:24:42.467
That's a terrible,
terrible thing for you to live with.

01:24:44.003 --> 01:24:47.404
But you're not unlovable, child.

01:24:47.507 --> 01:24:49.805
There's love all around you.

01:24:53.713 --> 01:24:56.375
Gimme your hand.

01:25:03.253 --> 01:25:06.814
<i>I started takin' care of Deborah</i>
<i>when she was nine, back in Virginia.</i>

01:25:06.924 --> 01:25:08.915
<i>Over seven years.</i>

01:25:09.026 --> 01:25:12.962
<i>Till my grandmama died</i>
<i>and left me this place.</i>

01:25:13.063 --> 01:25:16.521
That's why June
resented you at first.

01:25:16.633 --> 01:25:20.364
She never got over me
workin' in your mama's house.

01:25:20.471 --> 01:25:22.371
How did my mother get down here?

01:25:24.475 --> 01:25:28.036
She had an old friend from high school,
moved to Sylvan.

01:25:28.145 --> 01:25:32.172
Told her there were jobs,
and men back from the war.

01:25:32.282 --> 01:25:34.250
So she moved.

01:25:34.351 --> 01:25:36.410
I think it was 'cause of me though.

01:25:36.520 --> 01:25:39.284
I just think she wanted me nearby.

01:25:39.390 --> 01:25:43.952
So my mother came to Sylvan,
met T. Ray and got married.

01:25:44.061 --> 01:25:45.961
That's right.

01:25:46.063 --> 01:25:48.122
But what I don't get
is why she married him.

01:25:50.000 --> 01:25:54.664
I think Deborah liked the fact
that he was decorated in the war.

01:25:54.772 --> 01:25:56.672
She thought he was brave.

01:25:56.774 --> 01:25:58.833
Said he treated her like a princess.

01:25:58.942 --> 01:26:01.536
It's not the same T. Ray.
I can tell you that right now.

01:26:03.747 --> 01:26:07.239
You know, Lily,
people can start out one way...

01:26:07.351 --> 01:26:12.516
<i>and by the time life get through with 'em,</i>
<i>end up completely different.</i>

01:26:12.623 --> 01:26:16.719
<i>I mean, I don't doubt that he started off</i>
<i>lovin' her. Fact, he worshipped her.</i>

01:26:16.827 --> 01:26:22.026
<i>But after about six months or so,</i>
<i>her love wore off.</i>

01:26:22.132 --> 01:26:24.396
But she married him?

01:26:24.501 --> 01:26:27.902
<i>But if the love had worn off,</i>
<i>why did she marry him?</i>

01:26:29.873 --> 01:26:33.365
Honey, Deborah was pregnant.

01:26:33.477 --> 01:26:35.377
That's why.

01:26:42.252 --> 01:26:44.220
She called me
soon after you were born.

01:26:44.321 --> 01:26:48.223
<i>I got letters and phone calls,</i>
<i>mostly about you.</i>

01:26:48.325 --> 01:26:52.921
How you were sittin' up
and takin' your first steps.

01:26:53.030 --> 01:26:55.464
<i>Playin' patty-cake.</i>

01:26:56.800 --> 01:27:01.134
<i>But then the letters</i>
<i>start comin' less and less.</i>

01:27:01.238 --> 01:27:03.798
And one day she called me up...

01:27:03.907 --> 01:27:06.774
and she said she was leavin' T. Ray.

01:27:06.877 --> 01:27:09.038
- Thank you.
- Yes, ma'am.

01:27:09.146 --> 01:27:12.309
<i> When I picked her up</i>
<i>from the bus station...</i>

01:27:12.416 --> 01:27:14.316
<i>she didn't even look like herself.</i>

01:27:15.586 --> 01:27:17.486
<i>She had gotten so thin.</i>

01:27:17.588 --> 01:27:20.682
I was with her when you picked her up
from the bus station, right?

01:27:23.093 --> 01:27:25.027
<i>She brought me along, didn't she?</i>

01:27:28.465 --> 01:27:30.831
<i>No. She came by herself, honey.</i>

01:27:34.605 --> 01:27:37.335
<i>Why?</i>

01:27:37.441 --> 01:27:39.341
Why didn't she bring me?

01:27:41.645 --> 01:27:45.342
All I know, Lily,
is she was fallin' apart.

01:27:45.449 --> 01:27:47.349
Depressed people do things
they wouldn't ordinarily do.

01:27:47.451 --> 01:27:50.818
It was easy for her to leave me
'cause she never wanted me in the first place.

01:27:50.921 --> 01:27:52.821
Lily.

01:27:54.892 --> 01:27:57.725
<i>After she was here</i>
<i>for a few months...</i>

01:27:57.828 --> 01:28:01.525
and started feelin' better, she...
she start talkin' about how much she missed you.

01:28:03.467 --> 01:28:05.697
Then she went back
to Sylvan to see you.

01:28:06.803 --> 01:28:09.397
She was just comin' for her things.

01:28:09.506 --> 01:28:13.306
- I believe she came back for you.
- I'm goin' to bed.

01:28:13.410 --> 01:28:14.900
<i>Lily!</i>

01:28:15.012 --> 01:28:18.140
Now your mama
made a terrible mistake.

01:28:18.248 --> 01:28:20.148
But I believe she tried to fix it.

01:28:20.250 --> 01:28:22.150
Good night.

01:28:27.257 --> 01:28:30.055
Damn it, Deborah.

01:28:43.340 --> 01:28:44.898
I hate you!

01:28:45.008 --> 01:28:47.602
I hate your guts!

01:29:06.396 --> 01:29:08.864
Why didn't you love me?

01:30:19.403 --> 01:30:21.303
Tiburon.

01:30:25.075 --> 01:30:26.975
Lily.

01:30:30.781 --> 01:30:33.011
What in Mary's name happened here?

01:30:37.654 --> 01:30:39.554
Answer me.

01:30:47.030 --> 01:30:49.521
T. Ray was right about my mother.

01:30:51.768 --> 01:30:53.668
She left me.

01:30:59.576 --> 01:31:02.238
<i>Hi.</i>

01:31:02.346 --> 01:31:04.246
Hi.

01:31:04.348 --> 01:31:07.283
I brought some
of your mama's belongings.

01:31:12.482 --> 01:31:16.680
It's just a handful of things your mama left
when she went back to get you.

01:31:19.522 --> 01:31:21.513
Been in this box...

01:31:22.992 --> 01:31:25.187
10 years, I guess.

01:31:27.564 --> 01:31:29.691
You really loved her.

01:31:33.870 --> 01:31:37.271
It was complicated.
But, yes, I did.

01:31:38.374 --> 01:31:41.275
How was it complicated?

01:31:41.377 --> 01:31:43.709
I was her nanny.

01:31:43.813 --> 01:31:47.044
Things were different
in her world than mine.

01:31:49.752 --> 01:31:53.210
We like to think
that love is pure and limitless.

01:31:53.323 --> 01:31:57.589
But love like that
can't exist in a hateful time.

01:32:00.163 --> 01:32:02.996
But she made me love her anyway.

01:32:05.835 --> 01:32:09.498
There is no perfect love, Lily.

01:32:26.856 --> 01:32:29.188
Your mama's pocket mirror.

01:32:30.860 --> 01:32:35.058
If you look in here,
you see your mama looking back at you.

01:32:56.886 --> 01:32:58.820
Well, I'll be.

01:33:05.294 --> 01:33:08.525
She was wearin' that pin
the day she got here.

01:33:25.148 --> 01:33:27.173
There's just one last thing.

01:34:09.025 --> 01:34:11.516
Hey.

01:34:11.627 --> 01:34:13.595
Hey.

01:34:23.673 --> 01:34:25.766
- What happened to you?
- What about it?

01:34:25.875 --> 01:34:28.241
It changed you, didn't it?

01:34:33.216 --> 01:34:37.585
Sometimes, Lily, l...

01:34:37.687 --> 01:34:39.587
I get so angry.

01:34:40.957 --> 01:34:43.187
I just want to kill somethin'.

01:34:43.292 --> 01:34:46.159
The men that took you...

01:34:46.262 --> 01:34:48.662
they're angry like that too.

01:34:48.765 --> 01:34:50.926
Makes 'em mean.

01:34:53.236 --> 01:34:55.761
You have to promise me, Zach,
that you won't be like them.

01:34:55.872 --> 01:34:58.136
I don't want to.

01:34:58.241 --> 01:35:00.766
Me either.

01:35:26.969 --> 01:35:29.802
No way I'm not
becomin' a lawyer now.

01:35:31.641 --> 01:35:34.769
I'm gonna be one of them drum majors
Dr. King talks about.

01:35:34.877 --> 01:35:37.004
I know you will.

01:35:37.113 --> 01:35:41.982
And... 10, maybe
15 years from now...

01:35:43.252 --> 01:35:45.152
we'll be at your book signin'.

01:36:03.372 --> 01:36:06.466
So don't forget our story, all right?

01:36:08.444 --> 01:36:10.309
I won't.

01:36:21.257 --> 01:36:25.023
<i>I have you know I am now a registered voter.</i>

01:36:25.127 --> 01:36:27.322
- Really?
- I'll be castin' my vote for...

01:36:27.430 --> 01:36:29.364
Lyndon Johnson and Hubert Humphrey.

01:36:35.004 --> 01:36:37.165
I love you, Miss Rosaleen.

01:36:51.487 --> 01:36:54.217
- Neil.
- Hello, ladies.

01:37:12.508 --> 01:37:14.373
Hi.

01:37:14.477 --> 01:37:17.344
Hi.

01:37:17.446 --> 01:37:21.382
Didn't you call me here to talk?
I'm a little busy.

01:37:21.484 --> 01:37:23.401
You ain't the only one busy.

01:37:23.402 --> 01:37:25.318
I'm just supposed to stand
here and watch how busy you are?

01:37:25.421 --> 01:37:26.752
No.

01:37:34.397 --> 01:37:37.332
I was...

01:37:41.404 --> 01:37:44.271
I was wonderin' if you'd be
willin' to ask again.

01:37:44.373 --> 01:37:46.568
Ask what?

01:37:49.979 --> 01:37:52.072
This supposed to be funny?

01:38:02.191 --> 01:38:04.819
June Boatwright, will you marry me?

01:38:09.699 --> 01:38:11.599
Yes.

01:38:11.701 --> 01:38:13.794
Yes?

01:38:15.071 --> 01:38:16.971
Yes? Yes?

01:38:17.073 --> 01:38:19.701
Yes.

01:38:23.446 --> 01:38:26.540
She said yes.

01:38:26.649 --> 01:38:28.810
- Oh, my God.
- Good for you.

01:38:28.918 --> 01:38:30.909
Come on. We're goin' to
the jewelry store right now...

01:38:31.020 --> 01:38:33.181
pickin' out a ring before you
change your mind, all right?

01:38:33.289 --> 01:38:35.416
What? You don't already have one?

01:38:35.524 --> 01:38:37.424
Girl, come on.

01:38:37.526 --> 01:38:39.790
How come you don't have one?

01:39:08.224 --> 01:39:11.682
Well, well, well.
Look who's here.

01:39:14.530 --> 01:39:16.521
Won't you come in?

01:39:22.838 --> 01:39:25.068
<i>Well, all right, goddamn it.</i>

01:39:25.174 --> 01:39:28.940
<i>You wanna pretend</i>
<i>I'm making a social visit, we'll pretend.</i>

01:39:29.045 --> 01:39:31.843
I'm gonna take you out of here nice and quiet
or kickin' and screamin'.

01:39:31.947 --> 01:39:34.006
<i>Don't matter which one to me.</i>

01:39:34.116 --> 01:39:36.084
Have a seat if you want to.

01:39:49.765 --> 01:39:51.790
So you been here the whole time?

01:39:53.002 --> 01:39:54.902
With colored women?

01:39:55.004 --> 01:39:58.030
- <i>Jesus Christ.</i>
- How'd you find me?

01:40:00.709 --> 01:40:03.439
That map on your wall.

01:40:03.546 --> 01:40:05.707
Came here, started askin' around.

01:40:05.815 --> 01:40:10.081
Some old lady secretary at the law office
was more than happy to fill me in.

01:40:13.556 --> 01:40:16.889
- Where's Rosaleen?
- She took off a long time ago.

01:40:35.377 --> 01:40:38.710
Where'd you get that?

01:40:38.814 --> 01:40:41.112
- Miss August gave it to me.
- Don't you lie to me.

01:40:42.218 --> 01:40:44.118
I'm not lyin'.

01:40:44.220 --> 01:40:46.654
She said it belonged to my...

01:40:49.892 --> 01:40:53.328
I gave that pin to your mama
on her 22nd birthday.

01:40:55.297 --> 01:40:58.095
Now you tell me right now.

01:40:58.200 --> 01:41:00.862
- How'd this August woman get it?
- You gave this to my mother?

01:41:00.970 --> 01:41:02.938
- Answer me.
- You did?

01:41:05.541 --> 01:41:08.533
This is where my mother came
when she ran away from us.

01:41:09.678 --> 01:41:11.873
She was wearin' it
the day she got here.

01:41:22.758 --> 01:41:25.852
Miss August used to take care of her
when she was a little girl.

01:41:36.105 --> 01:41:38.835
I looked for her
everywhere I could think.

01:41:40.943 --> 01:41:42.877
And she was right here.

01:41:44.413 --> 01:41:46.881
Jesus Christ, she was right here.

01:41:59.428 --> 01:42:02.261
Goddamn you, Deborah!

01:42:02.364 --> 01:42:04.229
You ain't leavin' me again!

01:42:04.333 --> 01:42:06.198
Get back here!

01:42:06.302 --> 01:42:08.497
T. Ray, it's me, Lily!

01:42:08.604 --> 01:42:10.595
Daddy!

01:42:26.088 --> 01:42:29.148
You... You look like her.

01:42:37.466 --> 01:42:40.731
My whole life's
been nothin' but a hole...

01:42:40.836 --> 01:42:43.669
where my mother should've been.

01:42:43.772 --> 01:42:45.967
It left me always achin'.

01:42:48.077 --> 01:42:50.272
But I never thought about
what it did to you.

01:42:59.355 --> 01:43:01.949
- We're goin' home.
- I'm stayin' here.

01:43:05.227 --> 01:43:07.991
<i>You think I'm gonna</i>
<i>walk out of here and leave you?</i>

01:43:08.097 --> 01:43:10.088
I don't even know these damn people.

01:43:10.199 --> 01:43:12.099
I know them.

01:43:13.269 --> 01:43:15.396
And August Boatwright
is a good person.

01:43:15.504 --> 01:43:18.234
<i>Now, what makes you think</i>
<i>she'd even want you here?</i>

